Filter  39 out of 69 studies at least used a preprocessing filter, 31 of which used a low-pass filter among which 15 used the Butterworth low-pass filter. Note that preprocessing filters add to the latency in data processing, which is undesirable in a real-time system.
 Application 
Insole pressure sensors Only six out of 28 studies related to IPS used any sort of preprocessing/filtering. Instead, these studies relied directly on the raw signal from the IPS, likely contributing to shorter latency, an advantage when it comes to real-time systems.
